original: Lundh, David Martin Emanuel, kyrkoherde, Löttorp, f. 29/9/96 i Norra Ljunga, Jönköp. 1., av kyrkoh. Johannes L. o. Esther Bexell G. 25 m. Sophiasystern Siri Ohl&son. Barn: Stephan f. 27, Ursula 30. — Stud:ex. i Upps. 18, jur. stud. v. Upps. univ. 19-23, teol. fil. ex. i Gbg 25, teol. kand. i Upps., prakt. teol. prov 28, prästv. f. Växjö stift 29. Tjg. s. past :adj. i Döderhult o. vik. ständ. adj. i Urshult, ständ. adj. där 30, v. pastor i Högby 32-33, kyrkoh. där sed. 33. Ombud f. miss :’styr. sed. 37, ordf. i kyrkostämma, skolstyr. o. Högby-Källa RK-krets.
translated:
Lundh, David Martin Emanuel, parish priest, Löttorp, born September 29, 1896, in Norra Ljunga, Jönköping County. Son of the parish priest Johannes L. and Esther Bexell. Married to his cousin Sophia's sister, Siri Ohlsson. Children: Stephan, born in 1927, and Ursula, born in 1930. 

Education: Matriculation examination in Uppsala in 1918, studied law at Uppsala University from 1919 to 1923, theological philosophy examination in Gothenburg in 1925, theological candidate in Uppsala, practical theology examination in 1928. Ordained as a priest for the Växjö diocese in 1929.

Employment: Temporary assistant priest in Döderhult and deputy permanent assistant priest in Urshult. Became permanent assistant priest in Urshult in 1930 and vicar in Högby from 1932 to 1933. Appointed parish priest in Högby since 1933. 

He served as a representative for the mission board since 1937 and served as chairman in the church assembly, school board, and Högby-Källa RK district.
